E[X^2]=E[X(X-1)]+E[X]=\sum_{x=0}^k x(x-1)\frac{k!}{x!(k-x!)}p^x(1-p)^{k-x}+kp=
=k(k-1)p^2\sum_{x=2}^k \frac{(k-2)!}{(x-2)!(k-x!)}p^{x-2}(1-p)^{k-x}+kp=
=k(k-1)p^2\sum_{y=0}^m \frac{m!}{y!(m-y!)}p^{y}(1-p)^{m-y}+kp=k(k-1)p^2 \cdot 1+kp
